{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:43:29.954Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-600. Ids are prefix + 4 random base36 chars (~1.68M space); uniqueness enforced only via local on-disk idExists — blind to other branches and concurrent processes. Two agents branching from the same point can mint the same id for different items → silent identity collision surfacing as add/add merge conflict or ambiguous item. Same-disk sibling: pm-khdq (TOCTOU). Fix direction: entropy/length option or content-derived component + post-merge add/add collision detection in validate; document collision math per prefix length."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:43:29.954Z"}],"before_hash":"0181a76c06849b91405b73243723b1a7d76041c7fbe71263dc39e644cf0f4585","after_hash":"aab5edb80922765922400c22ecaa61a56ebd479baae0fa3befdfaefec3b63c67"}
