{"ts":"2026-07-19T16:38:22.190Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/2","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-19T16:38:22.190Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","text":"Greptile pre-push review 2b371c5d-ceb0-4948-8d0a-1b403891b2c5 identified an escalation-bound asymmetry and implicit duplicate-path ordering. Accepted with corrections: ID generation now caps collision escalation at ID_TOKEN_LENGTH_MAX using Math.min (the bot's Math.max suggestion would not enforce the bound), a 12-character collision exhausts exactly 32 attempts without minting an out-of-contract ID, and duplicate path arrays sort explicitly at their owning contract boundary."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T16:38:22.190Z"}],"before_hash":"85c66d96c6a9592b5aebb2bf0eb7ad2ce723dec7cc3d8fc5a29334d1b41379f7","after_hash":"a189d99b841272a1b3cb03dbf6d96d287049eeb03129b63f047cc76d77b825e5"}
